Inputs\:
 command - executes GatherAdvancedParametersforPatchHomeandDatabase.py

 Ignore SIDs - Optional\: List of SIDs that should not be patched.
 Inventory Files - Optional\: Comma-separated list of fully-qualified Oracle inventory files. If this parameter is not specified, the workflow looks for the oraInst.loc file in /etc and /var/opt/oracle.
 New OPatch Version - *Optional\: Provide the OPatch Version of the patch being applied. If provided MUST also provide Patch Number, Database Version, and Patch Name.
 OCM Response File - *Optional\: Path name of the Oracle Configuration Manager (OCM) response file. If not found on the target, this file is downloaded from the software directory on the HP DMA server. If left blank, a default response file will be created.
 OPatch Archive - *Optional\: The fully qualified path name of the OPatch Archive file required for this Critical Patch Update. If this file is not present, it will be downloaded. If this parameter value is not specified, the current OPatch version will be used.
 Oracle Home - *Required\: Fully qualified pathname of the Oracle Home where the patch will be applied.
 Patch Archive Location - *Optional\: Directory location where the zip archives will be extracted.
 Patch Download Location - *Optional\: The directory to which all downloaded files are copied from the software directory on the HP DMA server (only used if required files are not found on target but are found in the software directory).
 Patch Information File - *Optional\: Supplementary patch data supplied by support. If not found on the target, this file is downloaded from the software directory on the HP DMA server.
 Patch Name - *Optional\: Provide the patch name being applied. If provided MUST also provide Patch Number, Database Version, and OPatch Version.
 Patch Number - *Optional\: Provide the Patch Number of the patch being applied. If provided MUST also provide Patch Name, Database Version, and OPatch Version.
 Preparatory SQL Script - *Optional\: File name containing SQL statements that must be run before the database catalog update. This file is passed directly to SQLPlus and must be formatted as such. If not found on the target, this file is downloaded from the software directory on the HP DMA server.
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 CPU Archive Path - Fully qualified pathname of the Critical Patch Update Archive file downloaded for this update.
 Ignorable Oracle Errors - A comma-separated list of Oracle errors to be ignored when applying the patch to the database. This is in addition to the list of Oracle errors specified in the patch readme. Values are of the form ORA-nnnnn. Example\: ORA-04020,ORA-03113
 Ignore SIDs - Optional\: List of SIDs that should not be patched.
 Inventory Files - Comma-separated list of fully-qualified Oracle inventory files. If this parameter is not specified, the workflow looks for the oraInst.loc file in /etc and /var/opt/oracle.
 New OPatch Version - The OPatch Version of the patch being applied. If provided MUST also provide Patch Number, Database Version, and Patch Name.
 OCM Response File - Full pathname of the Oracle Configuration Manager (OCM) response file. Required for OPatch version 10.2.0.4.6 or newer.
 OPatch Archive - Fully qualified pathname of the OPatch Archive file required for this Critical Patch Update.
 Oracle Home - The ORACLE_HOME directory for this instance.
 Patch Archive Location - Location where patch will be unzipped
 Patch Download Location - Path to download patch if file not found
 Patch Information File - *Optional\: Supplementary patch data supplied by support. If not found on the target, this file is downloaded from the software directory on the HP DMA server.
 Patch Name - The patch name being applied. If provided MUST also provide Patch Number, Database Version, and OPatch Version.
 Patch Number - The Patch Number of the patch being applied. If provided MUST also provide Patch Name, Database Version, and OPatch Version.
 Preparatory SQL Script - *Optional\: File name containing SQL statements that must be run before the database catalog update. This file is passed directly to SQLPlus and must be formatted as such. If not found on the target, this file is downloaded from the software directory on the HP DMA server.
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.

 127f1003-da8d-497f-bc86-84a39def6afa.description=<pre>
 Purpose

Apply an Oracle Quarterly Patch Update to an Oracle Home and Databases.


 How to Use this Workflow

This workflow applies an Oracle Quarterly patch to an Oracle Home and databases. It also updates the OPatch version if the OPatch Archive file is specified.
This workflow only applies to single instance installations. It is not designed for Oracle Real Application Clusters (RAC).
Note that this workflow stops all processes running from the ORACLE_HOME in order to patch. This includes the Listener, which may be servicing instances outside this ORACLE_HOME.

All downloaded files are removed upon successful completion of the workflow.




 Additional Documentation

Additional information, including the _HP Database and Middleware Automation Support Matrix_ and solution pack user guides, are available via HP Live Network\:

"http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation"\:http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation

To access the documentation, click the RESOURCES link and enter your HP Passport credentials.
 Required Inputs

 Server Target - The desired target to run this flow against.
 Server Target Username - The user to login to the Server Target as.
 Server Target Password - The password to login as the Server Target Username.
 Download Source Host - The target host where the files needed for this flow can be downloaded from.
 Download Source Path - The path to where the files can be found on the Download Source Host.
 Oracle Home - *Required\: Fully qualified pathname of the Oracle Home where the patch will be applied.
 Patch Archive - *Required\: Relative path name of the patch archive file. Will check Archive Download Location for file and download if not found locally.
 Server.Become Routine - No description

 Optional Inputs

 Clean Code Base - Remove code base from target after execution (True || False).
 Clean JRE - Remove JRE from target after execution (True || False).
 Download From SA - Download binaries from SA (True || False). Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
 SA Folder Path - Location of binaries on SA. Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
 Debug Level - Set level of output [(least) 1-5 (most)]
 Ignore SIDs - Optional\: List of SIDs that should not be patched.
 Patch Number - *Optional\: Provide the Patch Number of the patch being applied. If provided MUST also provide Patch Name, Database Version, and OPatch Version.
 OPatch Archive - *Optional\: The fully qualified path name of the OPatch Archive file required for this Critical Patch Update. If this file is not present, it will be downloaded. If this parameter value is not specified, the current OPatch version will be used.
 Preparatory SQL Script - *Optional\: File name containing SQL statements that must be run before the database catalog update. This file is passed directly to SQLPlus and must be formatted as such. If not found on the target, this file is downloaded from the software directory on the HP DMA server.
 Patch Information File - *Optional\: Supplementary patch data supplied by support. If not found on the target, this file is downloaded from the software directory on the HP DMA server.
 Inventory Files - Optional\: Comma-separated list of fully-qualified Oracle inventory files. If this parameter is not specified, the workflow looks for the oraInst.loc file in /etc and /var/opt/oracle.
 Patch Archive Location - *Optional\: Directory location where the zip archives will be extracted.
 Patch Download Location - *Optional\: The directory to which all downloaded files are copied from the software directory on the HP DMA server (only used if required files are not found on target but are found in the software directory).
 New OPatch Version - *Optional\: Provide the OPatch Version of the patch being applied. If provided MUST also provide Patch Number, Database Version, and Patch Name.
 Patch Name - *Optional\: Provide the patch name being applied. If provided MUST also provide Patch Number, Database Version, and OPatch Version.
 OCM Response File - *Optional\: Path name of the Oracle Configuration Manager (OCM) response file. If not found on the target, this file is downloaded from the software directory on the HP DMA server. If left blank, a default response file will be created.
 Ignorable Oracle Errors - *Optional\: A comma-separated list of Oracle errors to be ignored when applying the patch to the database. This is in addition to the list of Oracle errors specified in the patch readme. Values are of the form ORA-nnnnn. Example\: ORA-04020,ORA-03113

 127f1003-da8d-497f-bc86-84a39def6afa.f79c3954-20ed-4bb9-8d91-8db085d4a11b.description=Description\:

This step parses the Oracle inventory files that exists, or else it forwards the inventory information.

(1) If the inventory pointer files are specified and exist, parse these files extracting the contents.
(2) If and inventory file is specified and does not exist, ensure a valid specification.
(3) If no inventory file is specified, assign the appropriate default.

Dependencies\: Must run as the server superuser.

Return Code\: 

0 \= All files were found on the system.
1 \= Errors occured while checking files.

Inputs\:
 command - executes ParseOracleInventory.py
 Inventory Files - Optional\: Comma-separated list of fully-qualified Oracle inventory files. If this parameter is not specified, the workflow looks for the oraInst.loc file in /etc and /var/opt/oracle.
 Oracle Account - Optional\: Oracle user that will own the Oracle Home. This is required only if inventory does not exist.
 Oracle Home - Optional\: The ORACLE_HOME to use if more than one Home is in the inventory file(s).
 Server Wrapper - Required\: String to execute routine as server superuser.
 Server.Become Routine - No description
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 Cluster Nodes - Comma-separated list of all nodes where the Oracle Home is deployed.
 CRS Account - The OS owner of the ORA_CRS_HOME.
 CRS Active Version - The active CRS version.
 CRS Group - The Oracle group used for the ORA_CRS_HOME installation.
 CRS Home - The last ORA_CRS_HOME location in the inventory file.
 CRS Home Name - The name of the ORA_CRS_HOME as recorded in the inventory.
 CRS Nodes - Comma-separated list of all nodes where the Oracle Clusterware is deployed.
 Inventory Groups - Comma-separated list of fully-qualified inventory groups. One for each Inventory Pointer.
 Inventory Locations - Comma-separated list of fully-qualified inventory pathname directories.
 Inventory Pointers - Comma-separated list of fully-qualified inventory pointer files.
 Oracle Account - Oracle user that will own the Oracle Home.
 Oracle Group - The Oracle group used for the ORACLE_HOME installation
 Oracle Home - The last ORACLE_HOME located in the inventory file or the user-inputted Oracle Home.
 Oracle Home Info - Dictionary list of all information discovered in the supplied inventory file(s).
 Oracle Home Name - The name of the ORACLE_HOME as recorded in the inventory.
 Oracle Listener Account - The OS owner of the ORACLE_HOME of the relevant listener.
 Oracle Version - Version of the Oracle Home.
 SQLPlus Version - Version of SQLPlus from Oracle Home.
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.
